I can't find an original name
text:
Why is it so difficult to find an original good-sounding name for a project?

A name that can be read and sound great in lots of languages, even if it means that there will be multiple pronunciacions.

After giving it some thought I wanted to do something a bit different. I'm settling on a 4 characters name: 2 letters and 2 figures. Do you think it might be original enough or are there already countless famous brand that have that same formula?

YC 22 ?

Ask HN: Is this a safe place to share?
text:
Hi, I have a project/idea for a mobile app and I'd like some random feedback, but not so random: from people who have a sensibility to imagine the vision of a product, that can see if it has some sort of potential. In fact I wanted to share a pitch deck on Reddit but I'm afraid someone could copy it. Of course a project shouldn't be so easy to copy but that thought is right for the final app. For a UX/UI designer it shouldn't take a lot to build an MVP or just a mock up with Figma. I'm just a regular person that had an idea which I believe is a bit of a game-changer. Is this a safe place to share a project?

Sorry if I sound a bit arrogant or stupid but I really care about this idea, it's like a child, you know? Feel free to give any advice or whatsoever.
